<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD6C80F3EE6E5CA6F189AF6" blockId="2.[166,609,697,725]" box="[166,609,697,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">
<heading id="D09E8188FFD6C80F3EE6E5CA6F189AF6" box="[166,609,697,725]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD6C80F3EE6E5CA6F189AF6" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[166,609,697,725]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Pechipogo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigilata">
<emphasis id="B91DEAF6FFD6C80F3EE6E5CA6CEF9AF1" bold="true" box="[166,406,697,724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">Pechipogo strigilata</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758
<emphasis id="B91DEAF6FFD6C80F3C17E5CA6F189AF6" bold="true" box="[599,609,697,723]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD6C80F3E9BE5896E979B30" blockId="2.[166,1225,762,980]" box="[219,1006,762,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Egg subspherical (
<figureCitation id="13522A61FFD6C80F3C34E5896FC89B30" box="[628,689,762,789]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[174,1233,174,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-5@1.[174,1233,174,1672]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1–6. Eggs of Nolidae, Chloephorinae: 1–5 — Pseudoips prasinana. Eggs of Erebidae, Hermeniinae: 6 — Pechipogo strigilata. Scale bars: 1, 3, 6 — 100 µm; 2, 5 — 1000 µm; 4 — 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453436" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453436/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">fig. 6</figureCitation>
), diameter 
<quantity id="4C919B01FFD6C80F3D76E5896EE99B31" box="[822,912,762,788]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
(n = 2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C373656FFFD6C80F3E9BE469696A9BF1" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD6C80F3E9BE4696E129BB0" blockId="2.[166,1225,762,980]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">
Chorion not ridged, marked by cells on two thirds surface (
<figureCitation id="13522A61FFD6C80F3DF3E4696E8D9B11" box="[947,1012,794,820]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1719,1741]" captionTargetBox="[174,1233,174,1671]" captionTargetId="figure-5@3.[174,1233,174,1672]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig.7–12. Eggs of Erebidae:Hermeniinae:7, 8 — Pechipogo strigilata; Hypeninae:9–11 — Hypena proboscidalis; Phytometrinae: 12 — Colobochyla salicalis. Scale bars: 7–11 — 10 µm; 12 — 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453438/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Clear transition between cells of micropylar area and remaining egg surface absent. Rosette with 12 long and narrow petalled cells (
<figureCitation id="13522A61FFD6C80F3FA6E4296F5E9B51" box="[486,551,858,884]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1719,1741]" captionTargetBox="[174,1233,174,1671]" captionTargetId="figure-5@3.[174,1233,174,1672]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig.7–12. Eggs of Erebidae:Hermeniinae:7, 8 — Pechipogo strigilata; Hypeninae:9–11 — Hypena proboscidalis; Phytometrinae: 12 — Colobochyla salicalis. Scale bars: 7–11 — 10 µm; 12 — 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453438/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Cells with thin walls, arranged irregularly on chorion. Aeropyles small, slightly expressed at walls junctions (
<figureCitation id="13522A61FFD6C80F3D5FE4096E229BB0" box="[799,859,890,917]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1719,1741]" captionTargetBox="[174,1233,174,1671]" captionTargetId="figure-5@3.[174,1233,174,1672]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig.7–12. Eggs of Erebidae:Hermeniinae:7, 8 — Pechipogo strigilata; Hypeninae:9–11 — Hypena proboscidalis; Phytometrinae: 12 — Colobochyla salicalis. Scale bars: 7–11 — 10 µm; 12 — 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453438/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD636E4FFD6C80F3E9BE4E9696A9BF1" blockId="2.[166,1225,762,980]" pageId="2" pageNumber="555">
R e m a r k. Egg surface cells located not like radial lines as those in 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD6C80F3DA7E4E969189B91" box="[999,1121,922,948]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Noctuidae</taxonomicName>
but chaotically, that typical for eggs of 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD6C80F3C54E4C96FC29BF1" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[532,699,954,980]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodontidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD6C80F3C86E4C96E1C9BF1" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1893" box="[710,869,954,980]" class="Insecta" family="Lymantriidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lymantriidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C694D67FFD6C80F3DDEE4C969779BF1" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[926,1038,954,980]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Arctiidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
